The global shipbuilding market is poised for substantial growth by 2028. The industry is experiencing a shift towards the construction of more eco-friendly vessels to comply with stringent environmental regulations. The rise in international seaborne trade is boosting the demand for container ships and bulk carriers. Container ships are projected to dominate the market due to the growing need for efficient transportation of goods. The increasing focus on offshore exploration and production activities is fueling the demand for specialized vessels such as LNG carriers and offshore vessels. Furthermore, the military sector is driving the market with investments in naval vessels to enhance security and defense capabilities.

